window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Two strangers - generations and oceans apart - have a chance to save each other in this moving and suspenseful novel about family secrets and the ineffable connections that lead us to one another.</b></p> <p>In a small Northern Italian village, nine-year-old Luca Taviano catches a stubborn cold and is subsequently diagnosed with leukemia. His only hope for survival is a bone marrow transplant. After an exhaustive search, a match turns up three thousand miles away in the form of a most unlikely donor: Joseph Neiman, a rabbi in Brooklyn, New York, who is suffering from a debilitating crisis of faith. As Lucaâ€™s young nurse, Nina Vocelli, risks her career and races against time to help save the spirited redheaded boy, she uncovers terrible secrets from World War II - secrets that reveal how a Catholic child could have Jewish genes.</p> <p>Can inheritance be transcended by accidents of love? That is the question at the heart of <i>This Magnificent Dappled Sea</i>, a novel that challenges the idea of identity and celebrates the ties that bind us together.</p>"; 
